{"sampleCodeDownload":{"kind":"sampleDownload","action":{"isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"Watch Video (21 min)","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2025\/250","type":"reference"}},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25-250-use-structured-concurrency-with-network-framework"]}],"sections":[],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-250-Use-structured-concurrency-with-Network-framework"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Network framework is the best way to make low-level network connections on Apple platforms — and in iOS, iPadOS, and macOS 26, it’s a perfect fit for your structured concurrency code. We’ll explore how you can make connections, send and receive data and framed messages, listen for incoming connections, and browse the network for services. We’ll also cover key best practices along the way."}],"metadata":{"title":"Use structured concurrency with Network framework","roleHeading":"WWDC25","role":"sampleCode","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25"]]},"kind":"article","schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"😱 “No Overview Available!”","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Be the hero to change that by watching the video and providing notes! It’s super easy:","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","type":"reference","isActive":true}]},{"level":2,"text":"Related Sessions","type":"heading","anchor":"Related-Sessions"},{"items":["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-268-Embracing-Swift-concurrency","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-228-Supercharge-device-connectivity-with-WiFi-Aware"],"type":"links","style":"list"}]}],"references":{"WWDC25-Icon.png":{"alt":null,"type":"image","identifier":"WWDC25-Icon.png","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-Icon.png","traits":["1x","light"]}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes":{"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes","title":"WWDC Notes","role":"collection","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Session notes shared by the community for the community."}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDCNotes.png"}]},"https://wwdcnotes.com/documentation/wwdcnotes/contributing":{"title":"Learn More…","url":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn More…"}]},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC25-268-Embracing-Swift-concurrency":{"kind":"article","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-268-Embracing-Swift-concurrency","title":"Embracing Swift concurrency","abstract":[{"text":"Join us to learn the core Swift concurrency concepts. Concurrency helps you improve app responsiveness and performance, and Swift is designed to make asynchronous and concurrent code easier to write correctly. We’ll cover the steps you need to take an app through from single-threaded to concurrent. We’ll also help you determine how and when to make the best use of Swift concurrency features – whether it’s making your code more asynchronous, moving it to the background, or sharing data across concurrent tasks.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25-268-embracing-swift-concurrency","role":"sampleCode"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC25-228-Supercharge-device-connectivity-with-WiFi-Aware":{"kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn how to create peer-to-peer network connections with Wi-Fi Aware. We’ll also cover how to share videos in real time, transfer large files, and control accessories with improved bandwidth and lower latency. And you’ll learn how to use DeviceDiscoveryUI, AccessorySetupKit, and the Network framework to use Wi-Fi Aware in your app."}],"title":"Supercharge device connectivity with Wi-Fi Aware","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25-228-Supercharge-device-connectivity-with-WiFi-Aware","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25-228-supercharge-device-connectivity-with-wifi-aware","role":"sampleCode"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC25":{"type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Xcode 26, Swift 6.2, iOS\/macOS\/tvOS\/visionOS 26."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"New APIs: "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Foundation Models"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"AlarmKit"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PermissionKit"},{"type":"text","text":", and more."}],"images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDC25-Icon.png"},{"type":"card","identifier":"WWDC25.jpg"}],"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc25","role":"collectionGroup","kind":"article","title":"WWDC25","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25"},"https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2025/250":{"checksum":null,"url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2025\/250","type":"download","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2025\/250"},"WWDC25.jpg":{"identifier":"WWDC25.jpg","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC25.jpg","traits":["1x","light"]}],"type":"image","alt":null},"WWDCNotes.png":{"variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDCNotes.png"}],"alt":null,"type":"image","identifier":"WWDCNotes.png"}}}